" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 23, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104ayx1665702860536.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ayx1665702860536.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ayx1665702860536.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"ayx1665702860536\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">A breakpoint is a marked code line, trigger, error, exception, or condition that\n      forces the application or component to break and the debugger to take control of execution. </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ayx1665702860536__p_d175178e1_d175179e1_d175180e1\">Set breakpoints to make your code easier to debug, to\n         notify you of a specific problem or occurrence, or because you expect to find a coding\n         error or exception that occurred in a particular location.</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ayx1665702860536__li_d53291e1_d53292e1_d53293e1\">A single breakpoint placed in a suspected trouble\n            spot allows the application to run uninterrupted until that point is reached.</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ayx1665702860536__li_d53294e1_d53295e1_d53296e1\">Multiple breakpoints allow you to break up your code\n            into more manageable pieces for testing.</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ayx1665702860536__li_d53297e1_d53298e1_d53299e1\">Conditional breakpoints allow the application to run\n            until specific conditions have been met. These conditions must be ones that the <code class=\"ph codeph\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"fzj1665702782147.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/fzj1665702782147.html\" title=\"Return the result of evaluating a conditional expression.\">$condition</a>\n</code> ProcScript function can handle.</li>\n</ul>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"ayx1665702860536__ul_o54_t5r_qwb\">\n<li class=\"li\">Error or exception related breakpoints allow the debugger to break on all or specific\n            errors and exceptions. For details, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"bxa1677053571070.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/bxa1677053571070.html\">Working with Error and Exception related breakpoints</a> and <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"lbe1677053515050.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/lbe1677053515050.html\" title=\"The following procedure allows developers to enable or disable Uniface debugger breakpoints based on the defined errors or exceptions break-on conditions on the Settings &gt; Error configuration tab.\">Configuring the Debugger Error and Exception behavior</a>.</li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"note tip note_tip\" id=\"ayx1665702860536__note_w2166ab1b5b5_w2167ab1b5_w2168ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Tip:</span> Add single breakpoints at various\n         locations in your ProcScript, and then edit these breakpoints individually. Otherwise, you\n         first need to know the exact location (ProcScript module, line number) and format expected\n         by the debugger.</div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ayx1665702860536__p_d175181e1_d175182e1_d175183e1\">Breakpoints constitute part of the debugger state.</p>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/fgr1665703523770.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Debugger State</a><p>The state of the Debugger consists of current settings, watches, and breakpoints. The current state can be saved as a named configuration for repeated use.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qrs1665702859881.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Working with breakpoints</a><p>Set breakpoints on ProcScript instructions, triggers, errors, or conditions.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3612035\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3612035\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Breakpoints Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 23, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 A breakpoint is a marked code line, trigger, error, exception, or condition that forces the application or component to break and the debugger to take control of execution. Set breakpoints to make your code easier to debug, to notify you of a specific problem or occurrence, or because you expect to find a coding error or exception that occurred in a particular location. A single breakpoint placed in a suspected trouble spot allows the application to run uninterrupted until that point is reached. Multiple breakpoints allow you to break up your code into more manageable pieces for testing. Conditional breakpoints allow the application to run until specific conditions have been met. These conditions must be ones that the $condition ProcScript function can handle. Error or exception related breakpoints allow the debugger to break on all or specific errors and exceptions. For details, see Working with Error and Exception related breakpoints and Configuring the Debugger Error and Exception behavior . Tip: Add single breakpoints at various locations in your ProcScript, and then edit these breakpoints individually. Otherwise, you first need to know the exact location (ProcScript module, line number) and format expected by the debugger. Breakpoints constitute part of the debugger state. Related Links Debugger State The state of the Debugger consists of current settings, watches, and breakpoints. The current state can be saved as a named configuration for repeated use. Working with breakpoints Set breakpoints on ProcScript instructions, triggers, errors, or conditions. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}